article.headline: Liberty 74, Winthrop 62
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. (AP) -- David Dees and Larry Blair combined for 29 points to lead Liberty to a 74-62 victory over Winthrop on Wednesday night. Liberty (14-12, 11-3 Big South Conference) won its seventh straight game and solidified its hold on first place in the conference race. Winthrop (14-11, 8-6), saw its three-game winning streak snapped. Winthrop got 15 points from both Marcus Cooke and Torrell Martin along with 13 points from Brandon Key. It was not nearly enough to offset Liberty's offensive attack that produced four double figure scorers and 51 percent field shooting.
